  "original_title": "\u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dda \u0d86\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbb \u0dc3\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dad\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0d85\u0dad\u0daf\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "India contributes to Sri Lanka's food security",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "News 18 India news agency stated that India has confirmed that it will participate in the proposed foreign aid summit that Sri Lanka is expected to hold along with China, India and Japan.",
        "News 18 news service reported that India may take steps to protect Sri Lanka's food security through emergency humanitarian aid.",
        "News 18 news service stated that India has assured that it will provide all necessary support for food and medicine through humanitarian aid in response to the requests received from Sri Lanka.",
        "News 18 reported that Sri Lanka has asked India for help due to rising inflation and shortage of essential goods and medicines.",
        "Sources said Sri Lanka sought India's help in debt restructuring, financial assistance and credit facilities to import essential goods, but fears of a food crisis have turned to its neighbor India for humanitarian aid, sources said."
      ],
